\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Overview of the finished control-comparison bundle. The panels show the full ranking by mean Sharpe, return-versus-drawdown trade-offs, the best representative in each controller family, and split-to-split Sharpe stability for selected methods. The main visual message is that CVaR-aware robust optimization is the strongest point-estimate controller in the new study, while simple rules remain competitive and RL is not the leading method.}}{12}{figure.caption.5}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:control_overview}{{2}{12}{Overview of the finished control-comparison bundle. The panels show the full ranking by mean Sharpe, return-versus-drawdown trade-offs, the best representative in each controller family, and split-to-split Sharpe stability for selected methods. The main visual message is that CVaR-aware robust optimization is the strongest point-estimate controller in the new study, while simple rules remain competitive and RL is not the leading method}{figure.caption.5}{}}
